            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The real reason seems to be a combination of this section in grdimage's parse function:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\tif (!GMT->common.n.active && (!Ctrl->C.active || gmt_is_cpt_master (GMT, Ctrl->C.file)))\r\n\t\t/* Unless user selected -n we want the default not to exceed data range on projection when we are auto-scaling a master table */\r\n\t\tn_errors += gmtinit_parse_n_option (GMT, \"b+c\");\r\n```\r\n\r\nand the changes in gmt_grdio.c. We clearly need the extra row/column and perhaps I can trick the min/max calculation by manipulating the pad temporarily.",
